review_blob: Wonderfully rich chocolate and coffee aroma.  Color is almost black with a reddish-brown hue.  Pours to a thin tan head that disappeared quickly.  Taste is nice, lots of coffee and chocolate with barley notes.  Palate is excellent, dryand slightly carbonated.  Overall an excellent stout.
Dark brown color with a thin tan head.  Aroma of coffee and wood smoke.  Tasty, roasted oats, caramel, and a touch of smoke.  Slight abv. finish.  Not a bad stout, nothing too spectacular though.

Aroma of citrus and pine, floral hints as well. Color is amber with a thin off-white head, slightly cloudy with particles floating around.  Strong hop flavor to start, but balanced with citrus and a touch of sweetness.  Finish is nice, the hops mellow out and a slight alcohol burn follows.  Very creamy palate that surprised me, provides a nice counter to the bitterness.  Overall its very good, for 85 IBUs its very well balanced and Ill drink it again.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Shared by BadgerBen.  Aroma was wheat and spices.  Cloudy yellow, with a white head.  Taste had notes of hops, malts, and a touch of fruit.  Not bad.

Shared by brewfiend.  Sweet caramel aroma.  Dark brown body with little head.  Taste was mostly malts with a touch fruit.  I didnt really notice the oak at all.  The 10.2% made an appearance in the finish but other than that stayed hidden very well.

Another growler via Skyview.  Aroma of bourbon and malts.  Taste threw me off, I expected more bourbon in the flavor due to the nose, but it was mostly masked by a smooth chocolate and coffee taste.  I really enjoyed this one.  Thanks again Skyview!
beer_name: Big Sky Ivan the Terrible Imperial Stout - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Aroma was fruity, kind of sweet with a touch of tartness.  Pours to a thick tan head over a dark amber color.  Taste was great, had a nice sugary sweet start that end ed in dry tart apple finish.  Very Good!
Another from Skyview.  Aroma was wheat and a slight sweet note.  Light gold color with a whitehead.  Smooth taste: yeast, honey, and a touch of citrus.  Not bad, a worthwhile Kolsch.
Thanks to Skyview for this one.  I couldnt quite place the aroma here, kind of like a stale basement or brewery .  Looks fine, typical gold color.  Tasted flat with vague spiced notes.

Smelled like cherries, almost to the point of "Starburst" or other candy.  Red color suits it well.  Very sweet cherry that leaves a thick syrupy taste on your tongue.  I could see having it after dinner but its nothing too notable.

Shared by Skyview.  Aroma was very light of chocolate.  The dark, almost black color with a thin white head.  Tasted of malts and with a faint smoked touch as well.  A touch watery and thin on the palate, but not bad.
Thanks to JK for this one.  Decent hops in the aroma.  Brown color with a light tan head.  Citrus and hops dominate the flavor with a dry and slightly bitter aftertaste.
beer_name: Carolina Beer Co. Cottonwood High Gravity Frostbite

review_blob: Light aroma of yeast and barley.  Head fell away quick to almost nothing.  Flavor wasnt bad, mostly sweet with a touch of malts.  Palate was kind of weak with a watery feel, nothing notable there.

It has a pleasant citrus and floral aroma.  Pours a huge fluffy white head over a hazy tan body.  The citrus aroma leads to a very defined grapefruit taste.  Not nearly the flavor I was expecting from it, kinda of dull without much complexity.  I did enjoy the overall tactile combination of the long-lasting fluffy head combined with the smooth citrus taste though.

Very VERY light aroma of hops and malt.  By looks alone this is a great beer, golden color with a creamy white head.  Unfortunately the taste doesnt live up to the look.  Smooth sweet grain flavor with a mild hop aftertaste.   Due to the low carbonation its a very smooth beer but it just doesnt have the complexity.  Overall its good for drinking after work but not a great beer.

Wonderful aroma, Malt, a nice rich coffee, and earthy undertones.  Appearance did it for me, Im a sucker for a thick dark beer with a nice tan head.  Overall a great beer, definitely one Ill be drinking more of.
Light aroma of coffee.  Dark brown color with a thin tan head.  For a coffee stout not too much coffee in the actual flavor, mostly caramel and malt.  Overall not bad, an average coffee stout.
Aroma is very light.  I loved the dark brown colour with a touch of red.  Slight taste of hops and a mild fruity tone to it.  Overall not a bad beer with dinner but nothing special.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale
